# Spotify Web API client ID for the now-playing / listening-history pairing.
#
# Resonark uses the Authorization Code + PKCE flow, so NO client secret is
# needed and nothing is stored server-side. A Client ID is a PUBLIC identifier
# (it ships in the built JS either way) — it is safe to commit / expose.
#
# Spotify is OPTIONAL; file + microphone capture work without it.
#
# To enable one-tap "Connect Spotify":
#   1. Create an app at https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#   2. Add Redirect URIs that exactly match where Resonark is served, e.g.
#      http://127.0.0.1:5173/ for local dev (Spotify requires 127.0.0.1, not
#      localhost, for http), and your deployed URL (e.g. https://resonark.ca/).
#   3. Put the Client ID below for local dev; for the deployed site set it as a
#      GitHub Actions repository variable named VITE_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID
#      (see docs/DEPLOY.md).
#
# If left blank, the app falls back to prompting each user for their own Client
# ID at runtime via the "Connect Spotify" button (stored only in their browser).
VITE_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
